README:
This dataset was obtained from the OpenfMRI project (http://www.openfmri.org).

Accession #: ds000172
Description: Physiological Contribution in Spontaneous Oscillations: An Approximate Quality- Assurance Index for Resting-State fMRI Signals

For validating the sensitivity of the proposed PICSO index (a new quality-assurance index for rs- fMRI) to functional connectivity, both fMRI dataset of phantom and human during resting state were acquired. The resting-state human dataset (n=12, age: 26.4  2.1 y, females/males: 6/6) was acquired at four image resolutions (1.31.32,222,333,and555mm^3). Moreover, a spherical water phantom was scanned using identical imaging protocols. Besides, T1-weighted structural images and B0 field map were acquired as well.
